Create a New Project Folder-->
    mkdir Home Service Booking System
Initialize a Node.js Project-->
    npm init -y
    this will create a package.json file in project Folder
Installing required packages-->
    npm install express ejs mongoose dotenv body-parser
    express--> web framework for Node.js
    ejs--> Templating engine for rendering dynamic HTML
    mongoose--> MongoDB library for Node.js
    dotenv--> Loads environment variable from a .env file
    body-parser--> Parses incoming request data
Setup Folder Structure-->
    mkdir views public routes models
    -it will create these folders
    touch .envm app.js
    -it will create empty .env file and app.js

install the necessary dependencies:-->
    npm install bcryptjs express-session mongoose connect-flash passport passport-local
    meanings-->
    bcryptjs → Hashes passwords securely.
    express-session → Maintains user sessions.
    connect-flash → Displays success/error messages.
    passport & passport-local → Handles authentication.
commands for github:-->
    git stauts
    git add .
    git add filename
    git commit -m "Your messages "
    git push origin main


